\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Eventually she gave up and defaulted to Ram, because who else was there? The Marquis brothers and their boys? One of their Guards? All of them were brutes who relished violence more than most - not to mention it meant dealing with Jillian. Perhaps Midwife Abi if she was done with the boys. Little Ricket? Each name was more difficult to imagine sitting next to Anna\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s than the last. But there was one which trumped them all:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Bart and Anna.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Absurd.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Bart and Despair, more like.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Never someone and Anna. Forever just Anna alone, for her beauty was a siren\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s song at the bottom of a bottomless well, enthralling all who wander near, drawing them downward into its depths, downward into sorrow and self-pity, teasing them with faint glimpses of the evanescent Anna. Bart was so deep now that the very thought of her was crushing.}
